gitCommit.subject: test(e2e): disable rate limits in test mode, add registration retry and clean e2e data handling
gitCommit.body:
test(e2e): disable rate limits in test mode, add registration retry and clean e2e data handling

- Bumped test‑mode rate‑limit multiplier from 10× to 1000× in `backend/internal/server/ratelimit/config.go`, effectively disabling throttling when `TEST_OAUTH=1`. Updated comment to reflect the change.
- Extended `e2e/helpers.ts::registerUser` with retry logic for HTTP 429 responses, using the server‑provided `retry_after_seconds` (or a fallback) and a maximum of three attempts. Updated function comment accordingly.
- Removed the stale `rm -rf ./data-e2e` step from the `e2e` Makefile target; the data directory is now cleared as part of the Playwright `webServer` command.
- Adjusted `playwright.config.ts` to delete the `data-e2e` folder before launching the dev server, ensuring a fresh environment and that `TEST_OAUTH=1` is always set. Also dropped the explicit `workers` override (CI now uses the default single worker).
- Updated `e2e/AGENTS.md` with a new “Parallelism and Resource Contention” section documenting the 1000× rate‑limit boost, retry behavior, and cleaning of the `data-e2e/` directory.
- Minor housekeeping: removed an unnecessary line in `Makefile` and updated related comments.

- Bumped test‑mode rate‑limit multiplier from 10× to 1000× in `backend/internal/server/ratelimit/config.go`, effectively disabling throttling when `TEST_OAUTH=1`. Updated comment to reflect the change.
- Extended `e2e/helpers.ts::registerUser` with retry logic for HTTP 429 responses, using the server‑provided `retry_after_seconds` (or a fallback) and a maximum of three attempts. Updated function comment accordingly.
- Removed the stale `rm -rf ./data-e2e` step from the `e2e` Makefile target; the data directory is now cleared as part of the Playwright `webServer` command.
- Adjusted `playwright.config.ts` to delete the `data-e2e` folder before launching the dev server, ensuring a fresh environment and that `TEST_OAUTH=1` is always set. Also dropped the explicit `workers` override (CI now uses the default single worker).
- Updated `e2e/AGENTS.md` with a new “Parallelism and Resource Contention” section documenting the 1000× rate‑limit boost, retry behavior, and cleaning of the `data-e2e/` directory.
- Minor housekeeping: removed an unnecessary line in `Makefile` and updated related comments.
